                    <h5>SAMANTHA</h5>
                    <p>Samantha Baldwin has been delving into Yoga philosophy since she was 17. Alongside her English degree, she took as many Eastern Religion courses as the University would allow including a level 1 Sanskrit course. Her deep fascination with Hinduism and its mythology drew her to 200+ hr. Yoga Teacher Training in 2012 where she graduated from Yoga Passage in 2013.</p>
                    <p>She also has a deep passion for working with moms, babies and all things relating to birth. She received her birth and post-partum doula training in 2003 and was certified as a prenatal and post-natal yoga teacher in 2014. She has also deepened her overall personal yoga practice as well as her teaching practice in 2014 by becoming a certified Yoga Nidra teacher.</p>
                    <p>Her classes often include Crystal Tones’ Crystal Healing Bowls as well as Young Living oils. She is an explorer of the unseen and her curiosity and exploration makes each class an inner adventure.</p>
                    <p>Can’t wait to see you on the mat! Hari Om Tat Sat.</p>
