                    <h5>SARAH</h5>
                    <p>I am a political scientist; art historian; PR professional with the Bad Girls Club YYC; world traveler; Etch-A-Sketch Artist; a unique individual with an authentic personality (yes, that’s right, an Etch-A-Sketch Artist). I am fairly new to teaching physical asana but certainly not a stranger to yoga. Yoga is life. I had my world literally flipped upside down in 2012 after going on a yoga retreat to Costa Rica with teacher Alice Hong (The trip ended with a bungee jumping off a bridge into a river. Since then, I can say inversions are easy). Costa Rica is a turning point in both my personal and spiritual practice. Shortly after returning from Costa Rica I was approached by my long time mentors and teachers, Lisa Whitford and Curran Watts, to take a teacher training with Define Yoga in Brazil, 2013. I have had an undeniable calling towards becoming a yoga teacher – it is just about time I answered the call. I like to combine colorful analogies with physical movement in a practice that is both yin and yang; fun and accessible to everyone.</p>
