                    <h5>BRANDY</h5>
                    <p>Brandy has been practicing yoga for more than a decade, exploring a variety of yoga styles, including Iyengar, Hatha, and Ashtanga. By focusing on alignment within the postures and using props to modify the practice, Brandy leads a gentle yoga class that is accessible for everyone and every body – regardless of level of experience, previous injuries or current abilities.</p>
                    <p>Brandy completed her Yoga Teacher Training at Yoga Passage in 2009. She completed her first Pre- and Postnatal Yoga Teacher course while eight months pregnant with her daughter, in August 2011, and her second in March and April 2012.</p>
                    <p>As a new mom herself, Brandy knows just how important a regular yoga practice can be to support your journey through motherhood – from pre-conception throughout baby’s first years. Yoga provides some time to reconnect with your body, relax the mind and quiet anxious or stressful thoughts, and to nurture both yourself and your baby-to-be.</p>
