                    <h5>GARY</h5>
                    <p>After many years working in the Oil and Gas industrY, I decided to take my personal yoga practice to another level by undertaking the 250hr teacher training course in SeptembeR 2012 at  Yoga Passage in Calgary.</p>
                    <p>During the course it became clear that the knowledge and experience I was gaining, significantly deepened my practice and also offerED me a much more rewarding, enjoyable and fulfilling vocation than that offered in the corporate world. I first started practicing yoga in 2000 to complement a life long passion for distance running. After seeing the greater depths that yoga had to offer; physically, mentally, spiritually and philosophically, it became quite easy for me to make yoga a major part of my life. </p>
                    <p>My main interests in yoga as a practice are many – I want to ‘spread the word’ to athletes as to the many benefits that yoga can bring; I love taking time to teach people so that they can enjoy learning in a safe and supportive environment and quickly develop their own practice. I relish adding challenging elements to a practice: balances, inversions and core work, but I also love to take time to explore the asanas fully, in hatha, yin and restorative sequences and further into nidra and meditation.</p>
                    <p>Hopefully I can share a practice with you in the very near future!</p>
